      ELEM: nodeName="h2"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="Preformatted Text"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="

Preformatted text is a good way to completely escape any and all formatting.  It also makes the output monospace (like the "
      ELEM: nodeName="code"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="code"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=" tag) and additionally it preserves the linebreaks.  Unfortunately it cannot uniformly guarantee the status of the line wrapping, so variance may occur between different emission mediums.

