"
      ELEM: nodeName="h1"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="More Complex Tags"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="

These tags make use of definable attributes or are otherwise related to each other.  They offer more powerful formatting, but are more difficult to use.

"
      ELEM: nodeName="h2"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="Heading Tags"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="

Heading tags are used to make text larger and like a section or chapter header.  They also relay information to the table of contents macro, so they facilitate the automatic generation of a table of contents that you can insert anywhere in the document.

There are six defined heading tags, though you can use an abstracted tag to go still further (or if you dislike the more compact named tags for some reason).

"
      ELEM: nodeName="table"
            ATTR: nodeName="align" nodeValue="right"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="right"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
         ELEM: nodeName="row"
            ELEM: nodeName="cell"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="<h1>Heading 1</h1>"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
         ELEM: nodeName="row"
            ELEM: nodeName="cell"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="<h2>Heading 2</h2>"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
         ELEM: nodeName="row"
            ELEM: nodeName="cell"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="<h3>Heading 3</h3>"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
         ELEM: nodeName="row"
            ELEM: nodeName="cell"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="<h4>Heading 4</h4>"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
         ELEM: nodeName="row"
            ELEM: nodeName="cell"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="<h5>Heading 5</h5>"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
         ELEM: nodeName="row"
            ELEM: nodeName="cell"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="<h6>Heading 6</h6>"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
         ELEM: nodeName="row"
            ELEM: nodeName="cell"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="<h level="#">Heading #</h>"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
      ELEM: nodeName="h2"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="Manual Breaks"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="

You can break a paragraph at any time using a "
      ELEM: nodeName="code"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="br"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=" tag.  This tag supports an option to perform an object-break, which will cause the text to continue below an object that wraps to the left or right of text.  To illustrate this:

"
      ELEM: nodeName="b"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="Before"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=":

"
      ELEM: nodeName="img"
            ATTR: nodeName="align" nodeValue="left"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="left"
            ATTR: nodeName="src" nodeValue="http://www.example.com/img.jpg"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="http://www.example.com/img.jpg"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="Talk about the image here.

Moving on, we're talking about something else but we're still associated with the image to the left.

"
      ELEM: nodeName="br"
            ATTR: nodeName="wrap" nodeValue="object"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="object"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
      ELEM: nodeName="b"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="After"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=":

"
      ELEM: nodeName="img"
            ATTR: nodeName="align" nodeValue="left"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="left"
            ATTR: nodeName="src" nodeValue="http://www.example.com/img.jpg"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="http://www.example.com/img.jpg"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="Talk about the image here.
"
      ELEM: nodeName="br"
            ATTR: nodeName="wrap" nodeValue="object"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="object"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="
Moving on, we're talking about something else and we're not longer associated with the image above.

"
      ELEM: nodeName="br"
            ATTR: nodeName="wrap" nodeValue="object"
               TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="object"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=[WS]
      ELEM: nodeName="b"
         TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue="Code"
      TEXT: nodeName="#text" nodeValue=":

<Before>:

<img align="left" src="http://www.example.com/img.jpg"/>Talk about the image here.

Moving on, we're talking about something else but we're still associated with the image on the left.

<br wrap="object"/>

<b>After</b>:

<img align="left" src="http://www.example.com/img.jpg"/>Talk about the image here.<br wrap="object"/>

Moving on, we're talking about something else but we're still associated with the image on the left.

<br wrap="object"/>
"
